vision_analysis.question_text: Thinking about your 2nd most recent LUNCH which was EATEN AT RESTAURANT / CAFÉ / FOOD OUTLET. Which of the following best describes the outlet where you purchased or obtained the main part of this meal?
clickable_elements: Fast Food / Takeaway that's not a chain (local or independent)
Café - Local or Independent and not part of a chain (can sit down in venue)
Hotel Restaurant (e.g. Novotel, Hilton, IBIS etc. but not a pub)
Food court outlet that's not a fast food chain
Chain Restaurant (e.g. Ribs & Rumps, Hogs Breath etc.)
Institution (e.g. Work, School, Sport/concert venue, Hospital supplied or Function Catering)
Stand-alone food outlet / sandwich bar not in food court, and has no seating
Café Chain (e.g. Coffee Club, Gloria Jeans etc.)
Restaurant that's not part of a chain
Fast Food Chain (e.g. McDonalds, Sumo Salad, KFC, Pie Face etc.)
